ciscoTransactionConnectionMIB.name: ciscoTransactionConnectionMIB

revisions.description: Imported Unsigned32 from SNMPv2-SMI instead of CISCO-TC.
The initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoTransactionConnectionMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W. Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: ctrc-dev@external.cisco.com
ciscoTransactionConnectionMIB.description: The MIB module for retrieving Cisco Transaction Connection configuration and status. Cisco Transaction Connection routes transactions between IBM CICS (Customer Information Control System) hosts and clients using the ISC (Inter-System Communication) protocol.

ctcLicense.name: ctcLicense
ctcLicense.description: An object containing a Cisco Transaction Connection license.

ctcLicenseState.name: ctcLicenseState
ctcLicenseState.description: The state of the Transaction Connection license. unconfigured : A license key has not been provided. notValidatedYet : A license key has been provided, but it cannot be validated until a server is created. When the first server is created, the license key is validated, changing the license state to one of the following. badKey : The content of ctcLicenseKey is not a valid license key. licenseOK : The license has been validated. expired : The expiration date of the license has passed.

ctcLicenseKey.name: ctcLicenseKey
ctcLicenseKey.description: A Transaction Connection license key. The field must be exactly 32 hexadecimal characters in length.

ctcLicenseMaxConn.name: ctcLicenseMaxConn
ctcLicenseMaxConn.description: The maximum number of connections allowed by the license. This field contains zero if the license is for an unlimited number of connections or if the ctcLicenseState is not licenseOK.

ctcLicenseCurrConn.name: ctcLicenseCurrConn
ctcLicenseCurrConn.description: Current number of connections in use. Normally, the value of this field should be less then or equal to the value in ctcLicenseMaxConn if it is not zero. However, when a license key is changed to decrease the maximum number ofconnections, the value of this field may temporarily exceed the limit. When this occurs, existing connections will not be deleted automatically to meet the new, smaller limit. New connections will be denied until the existing connections voluntarily disconnect.

ctcLicenseExpiration.name: ctcLicenseExpiration
ctcLicenseExpiration.description: The expiration date of the Transaction Connection license. This object contains a valid expiration date only if the license is not permanent.

ctcDestinationTable.name: ctcDestinationTable
ctcDestinationTable.description: A table containing Cisco Transaction Connection destination configurations.

ctcDestinationEntry.name: ctcDestinationEntry
ctcDestinationEntry.description: A row containing a Cisco Transaction Connection destination configuration.

ctcDestinationRemoteLUName.name: ctcDestinationRemoteLUName
ctcDestinationRemoteLUName.description: The Remote LU (Logical Unit) name of the destination target.

ctcDestinationModeName.name: ctcDestinationModeName
ctcDestinationModeName.description: The mode name of the destination target. In SNA, a mode name is the name used by the initiator of a session to designate the characteristics desired for that session, such as traffic pacing values, message length limits, and the class of service within the transport network.

ctcDestinationNumHits.name: ctcDestinationNumHits
ctcDestinationNumHits.description: The number of hits the destination target has received. A hit is registered each time a route is looked up. This means that every time a connection is established, one destination target of the route has its hit count incremented.

ctcRouteTable.name: ctcRouteTable
ctcRouteTable.description: A table containing Cisco Transaction Connection route configurations.

ctcRouteEntry.name: ctcRouteEntry
ctcRouteEntry.description: A row containing a Cisco Transaction Connection destination configuration.

ctcRouteOwningServer.name: ctcRouteOwningServer
ctcRouteOwningServer.description: The ctcServerIndex of the server that owns this route.

ctcRouteTransactionID.name: ctcRouteTransactionID
ctcRouteTransactionID.description: The transaction ID that this route handles.

ctcRouteDestinationName.name: ctcRouteDestinationName
ctcRouteDestinationName.description: The name of this route's destination.

ctcServerTable.name: ctcServerTable
ctcServerTable.description: A table containing Transaction Connection servers.

ctcServerEntry.name: ctcServerEntry
ctcServerEntry.description: A row containing a Transaction Connection server. This server routes APPC (Advanced Program-to-Program Communcations) data streams between TCP/IP clients and CICS hosts. Each server will have a unique IP address and port.

ctcServerIndex.name: ctcServerIndex
ctcServerIndex.description: The index of this server in the server list.

ctcServerListening.name: ctcServerListening
ctcServerListening.description: This object reflects whether or not the server is listening for connections. A return value of 'true' means the server is actively listening.

ctcServerIPAddr.name: ctcServerIPAddr
ctcServerIPAddr.description: This object reflects the IP address for which the server is listening for connections. If it is set to 0.0.0.0, then the server is listening on all IP addresses.

ctcServerPort.name: ctcServerPort
ctcServerPort.description: The port on which the server is listening for connections.

ctcServerDestinationName.name: ctcServerDestinationName
ctcServerDestinationName.description: This object reflects the name of this server's default destination.

ctcServerClientTimeout.name: ctcServerClientTimeout
ctcServerClientTimeout.description: This object reflects the period of time that a client end connection can remain idle before being dropped by a server. The maximum time is 24 hours. If set to 0, the server will never drop the connection due to a timeout event.

ctcServerHostTimeout.name: ctcServerHostTimeout
ctcServerHostTimeout.description: This object reflects the period of time that a host end connection can remain idle before being dropped by a server. The maximum time is 24 hours. If set to 0, the server will never drop the connection due to a timeout event.

ctcServerWindowSize.name: ctcServerWindowSize
ctcServerWindowSize.description: TCP window size for each connection of the Transaction Connection server.

ctcServerConnectionCount.name: ctcServerConnectionCount
ctcServerConnectionCount.description: The number of connections on this server at this moment.

ctcServerProgNameUpperCase.name: ctcServerProgNameUpperCase
ctcServerProgNameUpperCase.description: This object reflects whether or not the server will convert CICS program names to upper case. A return value of 'true' means the server will convert such names to upper case.

ctcConnectionTable.name: ctcConnectionTable
ctcConnectionTable.description: A table containing connection information. Each row reflects a client connection that is active at this moment.

ctcConnectionId.name: ctcConnectionId
ctcConnectionId.description: The ID of the connection object.

ctcConnectionServer.name: ctcConnectionServer
ctcConnectionServer.description: The ctcServerIndex of the server that owns this connection.

ctcConnectionState.name: ctcConnectionState
ctcConnectionState.description: The state of a connection object. reset : the connection is ready to process data closing : the connection is in the process of closing halt : the connection has halted due to an error condition receiving : the connection is receive normal data

ctcConnectionSessionCount.name: ctcConnectionSessionCount
ctcConnectionSessionCount.description: The number of sessions currently in use for the connection.

ctcConnectionClientIPAddr.name: ctcConnectionClientIPAddr
ctcConnectionClientIPAddr.description: IP address of client machine using this connection.

ctcConnectionClientPort.name: ctcConnectionClientPort
ctcConnectionClientPort.description: Port number used on client machine for this connection.

ctcConnectionTotalConversations.name: ctcConnectionTotalConversations
ctcConnectionTotalConversations.description: The number of conversations that have been processed by the connection.

ctcConnectionConnectTime.name: ctcConnectionConnectTime
ctcConnectionConnectTime.description: The moment when the connection was established.

ctcConnectionIdleTime.name: ctcConnectionIdleTime
ctcConnectionIdleTime.description: Amount of time the connection has gone without activity.

ctcConnectionTotalBytesRecvd.name: ctcConnectionTotalBytesRecvd
ctcConnectionTotalBytesRecvd.description: The total number of bytes received from client.

ctcTransactionTable.name: ctcTransactionTable
ctcTransactionTable.description: A table containing transaction information. Each row reflects a host transaction that is active at this moment.

ctcTransactionSessionId.name: ctcTransactionSessionId
ctcTransactionSessionId.description: The ID of the transaction session object.

ctcTransactionServer.name: ctcTransactionServer
ctcTransactionServer.description: The ctcServerIndex of the server that owns this transaction.

ctcTransactionConnectionId.name: ctcTransactionConnectionId
ctcTransactionConnectionId.description: The ID of the transaction session object's connection.

ctcTransactionState.name: ctcTransactionState
ctcTransactionState.description: The state of a connection object. reset : the transaction is ready to process data opening : the transaction is opening a connection sending : the transaction is sending data receiving : the transaction is receiving data exception : the transaction has encountered an error exceptionresponse : the transaction is awaiting an error response closing : the transaction is in the process of closing

ctcTransactionTPName.name: ctcTransactionTPName
ctcTransactionTPName.description: The transaction program name of the transaction. This is sometimes referred to as the TRANID in CICS.

ctcTransactionUserId.name: ctcTransactionUserId
ctcTransactionUserId.description: The user ID that was used to initiate the transaction.

ciscoTransConnMIBCompliance.name: ciscoTransConnMIBCompliance
ciscoTransConnMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Cisco Transaction Connection MIB

ciscoTransConnLicenseGroup.name: ciscoTransConnLicenseGroup
ciscoTransConnLicenseGroup.description: A collection of objects providing Transaction Connection license monitoring.

ciscoTransConnDestinationGroup.name: ciscoTransConnDestinationGroup
ciscoTransConnDestinationGroup.description: A collection of objects providing Transaction Connection destination monitoring.

ciscoTransConnRouteGroup.name: ciscoTransConnRouteGroup
ciscoTransConnRouteGroup.description: A collection of objects providing Transaction Connection route monitoring.

ciscoTransConnServerGroup.name: ciscoTransConnServerGroup
ciscoTransConnServerGroup.description: A collection of objects providing Transaction Connection server monitoring.

ciscoTransConnConnectionGroup.name: ciscoTransConnConnectionGroup
ciscoTransConnConnectionGroup.description: A collection of objects providing Transaction Connection monitoring.

ciscoTransConnTransactionGroup.name: ciscoTransConnTransactionGroup
ciscoTransConnTransactionGroup.description: A collection of objects providing Transaction Connection transaction monitoring.
